   <text>
      <body>
         <pb n="1r" facs="lf_pDas_1576_dai_lns235ms_a_r.jpg"/>
         <div xml:id="orig_div1" xml:lang="ara" type="invocation" rend="top centre">
            <p>هو
               <lb rend="empty"/><gap/>
               خلد اله تعلی مالکه اندر
            </p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="trans_div1" corresp="#orig_div1">
            <p>He [God] is
               <lb rend="empty"/><gap></gap>May God make his kingdom eternal</p>
         </div>

         <div xml:id="orig_div2" xml:lang="per" type="authorisation" rend="middle right and centre">
            <p><stamp type="seal"><mentioned>
                      غلام
                      <persName ref="#jahangir">جھانگیر</persName>
                      شاھ
                      <gap></gap>
                      یعقوب 
                      <date calendar="#hijri-shamsi">۹۸۲</date>
                      <gap/>
            </mentioned></stamp>
               <lb rend="empty"/>
            <lb rend="empty"/><stamp type="seal"><mentioned><gap></gap></mentioned></stamp></p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="trans_div2" corresp="#orig_div2">
            <p><stamp type="seal">Round black ink seal<mentioned><gap/>Yaqub, servant of <persName ref="#jahangir">Jahangir</persName> Shah<note>While it is possible that this is a reference to Mughal emperor <persName ref="#jahangir">Jahangir</persName>, this interpretation is uncertain as he would have been about five years old in the year the seal was issued.</note> <date calendar="#hijri-shamsi">982</date>
               <gap/></mentioned></stamp>
               <lb rend="empty"/>
            <lb rend="empty"/><stamp type="seal">Round black ink seal<mentioned><gap></gap></mentioned></stamp><note>Below and to the left of the first seal. Its position somewhat overlapped by the maintext is unusual.</note></p>
         </div>
         
         <div xml:id="orig_div3" xml:lang="per" type="maintext">
            <p>
               <lb/>چون مطیع السلام
               <persName ref="#jayantiDas">جینتی داس</persName>
               و
               <persName ref="#narharDas">نرھرداس</persName>
               وغیرہ دولتخواہ اند و در باب ابادانی و معموری پرگنہ
               <placeName ref="#pgDhar">دار</placeName>
               فی
               <gap/>
               <lb/><placeName ref="#mandu">مندو</placeName>
               اھتمام می نمایند بنابرین از ابتدای خریف
               <date calendar="#turkish">سیچقانیل</date>
               موازی دویست بیگه زمین
               افتادہ
               <lb/>از موضع
               <placeName ref="#gardawad">گرداود</placeName>
               وغیرہ از پرگنه مذکور در وجه انعام مطع اسلام 
               <persName ref="#jayantiDas">جینتی داس</persName>
               مذکور وغیرہ مقر شد باید که متصدیان
               <lb/>مھمات و معاملان پرگنه مذکور اراضی مذکور را
               <unclear>بتنخواه</unclear>
               واگذاشته بتصرف ایشان گذارند که
               باستطاعت خود
               <lb/>مزروع نموده حاصل آنرا صرف معاش خود نموده بدعاگوی دوام دولت بندگان حضرت
               <space/>
               مشغول باشند
               <lb/>و بعلت مالواجب و اخراجات
               <gap/>
               دیوانی مزاحمت عامل ایشان نرساند و آن مطع اسلامان در باب ابادانی
               <lb/>
               و معموری پرگنه مذکور چنان سعی نمایند که اثار دولتخواھی ایشانان بظھور رسد سنه
               <date calendar="#hijri-qamri"><num>۹۸۴</num></date>
            </p>
         </div>
         
         <div xml:id="trans_div3" corresp="#orig_div3">
            <p><lb/>Since Obedient to Islam <persName ref="#jayantiDas">Jayanti Das</persName> and <persName ref="#narharDas">Narhar[i] Das</persName> etc. are loyal and have
               demonstrated diligence in the populating and managing of <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_pargana">pargana</ref> <placeName ref="#pgDhar">D[h]ar</placeName> in
               <gap/>
               <lb/>[<ref type="glossary" target="#gl_sarkar">sarkar</ref>] <placeName ref="#mandu">Mandu</placeName>; on this basis, from the beginning of the autumn season of <date calendar="#turkish">Sichqan-il [Year of the Mouse]</date>, <measure type="land" unit="bigha" quantity="200">200</measure>
               <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_bigha">bighas</ref> of fallow land
               <lb/>from the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_mauza">mauza</ref> <placeName ref="#gardawad">Gardawad</placeName> etc. from
               the said <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_pargana">pargana</ref> is allocated to
               Obedient to Islam <persName ref="#jayantiDas">Jayanti Das</persName> etc. as <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_inam">inʿam</ref>. Officers
               <lb/>of the said <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_pargana">pargana</ref> must give over the said lands <unclear>as an assignment</unclear><note>While the term 'tankhwah' usually refers to pay, or to a jagir assigned in lieu of pay (see <ref type="bibl" target="#habib">Habib, The Agrarian System of Mughal India, p. 329</ref>), its usage here in the context of a grant of inʿam may refer more generically to any assignment on the land revenue. For this sense, see <ref type="bibl" target="#wilson">Wilson, Glossary, p. 509</ref>.</note> and
               transfer [the lands] into their [the assignees’] possession; so that getting
               these lands cultivated through their own efforts
               <lb/>[and] using the collections from these [lands] for their living expenses, they may
               occupy themselves with praying for the endurance of the good fortune of the servants
               of the Lord <space/>.
               <lb/>And the
               <unclear>officers</unclear>
               of the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_diwani">diwani</ref> should not trouble them on account of land tax and other taxes. And these [people who are] Obedient to Islam
               should
               <lb/>make such efforts for the populating and governing of the said <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_pargana">pargana</ref> [so] that
               their loyalty becomes evident.
               <date calendar="#hijri-qamri">Year 984</date>.
            </p>
         </div>

         <pb n="1v" facs="lf_pDas_1576_dai_lns235ms_a_v.jpg"/>

         <div xml:id="orig_div5" xml:lang="per" type="clericalNotes" rend="middle">
            <p><list><lb/>
